Percent identity refers to a quantitative measurement of the similarity between two sequences (DNA, amino acid or otherwise) ( DNA序列 氨基酸序列 等等 ). Closely related species are expected to have a higher percent identity for a given sequence than would more distantly related species, and thus percent identity to a degree reflects relatedness.
